"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"## How Thoreau improved my vision\\n\\n[![Eric Weiner](https://miro.medium.com/fit/c/56/56/2\\\\*lyhdcq0OSUfLCxmCQpr2TQ.jpeg)](https://ericweiner.medium.com/?source=post_page-----32fd0a4fd1ca-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[](https://ericweiner.medium.com/?source=post_page-----32fd0a4fd1ca-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[Eric Weiner](https://ericweiner.medium.com/?source=post_page-----32fd0a4fd1ca-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[](https://forge.medium.com/the-art-of-seeing-32fd0a4fd1ca?source=post_page-----32fd0a4fd1ca-----------------------------------)\\n\\n[Dec 20·5 min read](https://forge.medium.com/the-art-of-seeing-32fd0a4fd1ca?source=post_page-----32fd0a4fd1ca-----------------------------------)\\n\\n![](https://miro.medium.com/max/1400/0\\\\*68Iw4nlMi69ug\\\\_8M)\\n\\nPhoto by [Harry Quan](https://unsplash.com/@mango_quan?utm_source=medium\\\\&utm_medium=referral) on [Unsplash](https://unsplash.com/?utm_source=medium\\\\&utm_medium=referral)\\n\\nI thought my vision was pretty good. Not quite 20–20, but close. Then I read Thoreau.\\n\\nYes, *that *Thoreau. Forget what you may have read by or about the “hermit Concord.” He is misunderstood. His experiment on Walden Pond was about seeing. All the rest — the solitude, the simplicity — were means to this end.\\n\",\"timestamp\":1641036224,\"title\":\"The Art of Seeing - Forge\"},\"digest\":\"IhacuNkqViKVxVyRuOLqOpTYX160Jb1y7Vv-J_vd5w8\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0x7B952c47C13520acbcE482625517aD07bE28434C\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"0KWyq8xoq0Yo-FExLpV5xnshmfWntzBiZp2n3jm28aQ\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"3bhu46jU7lQ-SN2nuZ1hMl2L1D5-uiOY5gfCz5EnU9c\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"EFm9Xv-K5HIKTdXzVVXkNutPpmTqYmMjfoxVWRuvAngymWrmXKiOX2CcbVUDkk3sqzz78fKJu8N-pIC6GSHWsA\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0x29555bf35d30028a73df8183ea9d4e50703c2a2983c0766c0879c925c5afe1841abd1a1c54